21/02/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- UN war crimes tribunal chief prosecutor Serge Brammertz is arriving on Monday (February 21st) in Belgrade for meetings Tuesday with President Boris Tadic, the head of the national council for co-operation with the tribunal, Rasim Ljajic, and war crimes prosecutor Vladimir Vukcevic. The focus will be Serbia's efforts to locate and arrest the two remaining war crimes fugitives -- Ratko Mladic and Goran Hadzic. (Beta, Radio Free Europe, Tanjug, B92 - 21/02/11)
